lead_paragraph: Tokyo won the 2020 Olympics on its reputation for efficiency, but a string of blunders has now been compounded by the city's new governor halting relocation of the world's largest fish market, jeopardizing a road needed for the Summer Games.

headline.print_headline: Tokyo Olympics Plan Hits Roadblock Over Fish Market's Relocation
